			<h3 style="text-align: center; font-size: 30px; text-transform: capitalize;"><strong>And the winner is&#8230;..WordPress!</strong></h3>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">For me, I choose WordPress all the time. There are plenty of other website builders out there to choose from, but WordPress wins hands down for a number of reasons.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h3 style="text-align: left; font-size: 26px; text-transform: capitalize;"><strong>1. User Friendly &amp; Newbie Friendly </strong></h3>
<p>The WordPress platform is so easy to use. It&#8217;s intuitive and if you know how to use standard Microsoft programs such as Word or Excel, then chances are you&#8217;ll already know how to publish your own content on the site you&#8217;re about to build.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Another great thing about WordPress is that it can be easily customized with plugins, that can pretty much do anything to your site and make it exactly how you want it. You might want just a simple small business website or a complex e-com site with hundreds of products. WP can handle this.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h3 style="text-align: left; font-size: 26px; text-transform: capitalize;"><strong>2. Powerful </strong></h3>
<p>WordPress is extremely powerful and can run most types of sites. It&#8217;s a trusted platform for many of the busiest websites in the world. It can handle pretty much anything.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h3 style="text-align: left; font-size: 26px; text-transform: capitalize;"><strong>3. Responsive &amp; Mobile Friendly </strong></h3>
<p style="text-align: left;">With more and more people viewing sites on their phones and other mobile devices, it&#8217;s really important to have a site that is responsive to these digital demands. With WordPress, most themes come mobile friendly as standard.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h3 style="text-align: left; font-size: 26px; text-transform: capitalize;"><strong>4. It won&#8217;t cost you a thing! </strong></h3>
<p style="text-align: left;">WordPress is free. All you have to do is buy your domain and hosting and then you&#8217;re up and running before you can say &#8220;www.&#8221;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h3 style="text-align: left; font-size: 26px; text-transform: capitalize;"><strong>5. Plenty of lovely people to help you out. </strong></h3>
<p style="text-align: left;">WordPress is blessed with a vibrant and helpful community of developers who will be happy to help you out should you get stuck with anything to do with your WordPress site.</p>

